news.title: China Vanke stock, bonds resume their sell-off on liquidity concern
news.para: China Vanke's Hong Kong-listed shares fell 7.1%, having finished last week down 8.1%. The developer's Shenzhen-listed shares lost 4.7%, exacerbating last week's 3% decline.

news.title: Chicago: 'Mansion taxes' to fund homeless services stuck in legal limbo
news.para: Such citywide ballot measures are rare in the nation's third-largest city, but other cities, including Los Angeles, have approved similar so-called "mansion taxes."

news.title: ED questions Niranjan Hiranandani in FEMA probe case
news.para: Niranjan Hiranandani and his son Darshan Hiranandani were asked to join the investigation by the Enforcement Directorate (ED) at its office here as part of a probe being conducted against them under the Foreign Exchange Management Act (FEMA).

news.title: Maharashtra CM lays foundation of Mumbai metro line-12
news.para: Metro Line 12 incorporates a completely elevated structure with 19 stations along the 22.173 km route. The estimated cost of this project, expected to be completed by end-2027, is around Rs 5,865 crore, as per an official release.

news.title: Delhi LG approves draft policy for inter-departmental allotment of land
news.para: Delhi LG VK Saxena has approved the draft uniform policy for inter-departmental allotment of land, including subordinate departments and autonomous bodies.

news.title: Aaron Ville residents write to Gurugram deputy commissioner alleging harassment by the builder
news.para: In 2018, residents had filed a complaint to Haryana Electricity Regulatory Commission (HERC) against the developer for charging beyond the applicable electricity tariff.

news.title: REA India's revenue up 21% at Rs 238 crore in July-December 2023: CEO
news.para: REA India, which is part of Australia's publicly listed firm REA, is a full-stack real estate technology firm and owns two online classified advertisement platforms Housing.com and Makaan.com as well as housing brokerage PropTiger.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body waives off interest on property tax
news.para: This initiative aims to provide relief to taxpayers who are burdened by interest charges. As per govt guidelines, taxpayers can avail of this waiver by settling their total tax dues by March 31.

news.title: Odisha government hikes pension of construction workers
news.para: According to an official release, construction workers registered under the Odisha Building and Other Construction Workers' Welfare Board are eligible for the pension.

news.title: Make smart villages too along with smart cities: Union minister
news.para: The Union minister said, “I am turning Bela village, 30km from Nagpur, into a smart village. If this experiment succeeds, then we can replicate it everywhere.”

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority urges builders of nine projects to accept government package
news.para: YEIDA chairman Anil Kumar Sagar held a meeting at Yamuna Authority last week to discuss the issue of implanting the rehab package with builders.

news.title: Edelweiss Alternatives set to buy IT park in Bengaluru for over Rs 1,475 crore
news.para: This is the largest and first transaction for a complete buyout of an office tower so far this year. Edelweiss Alternatives is buying this asset through its rental fund, which is currently in the process of raising Rs 5,000 crore.

news.title: Now, nod to registry of plots & homes in regularised colonies in Haryana
news.para: On October 4, 2023, a notification was issued by DTCP for regularisation of these 21 colonies carved out on about 186 acres of prime land in different villages of Gurgaon, Manesar, Sohna, Pataudi and Farrukhnagar.

news.title: Online application must for Kolkata civic body's nod to new building plans
news.para: Manual application will be allowed only to seek approval of plans for additions and alterations to existing structures and reconstruction of insecure buildings, mayor Firhad Hakim said on Saturday.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board gets Rs 48 crore under transfer of property tax
news.para: The CEO added that another 20 crore is even now pending with the state govt and urged the govt to release the remaining TPT charges.

news.title: Odisha RERA asks builders to submit bank account details of projects
news.para: As per the rules, the promoters need to maintain a separate bank account for each of the housing projects if they have taken booking amount from the homebuyers.

news.title: Panvel civic body serves prior-to-seizure notices to 300 property tax defaulters
news.para: They include 101 industrial units, 107 non-residential properties and 100 residential properties. The civic body area has 3.50lakh properties. The property tax matter has reached the Supreme Court.

news.title: HC directs ED to probe promoters of 3C, berates Noida authority for 'acting like private trader'
news.para: Calling it a "classing case of conning", the court ordered the developers to cooperate with the ED and said the central agency "would be free to take any appropriate action against them as available under the law".

news.title: Documents related to projects should be delivered at headquarter: UP-RERA
news.para: According to this office order, promoters have been directed to deliver the documents related to project registration, extension, editing, etc., either personally or post, at UP-RERA Head Office, Lucknow.

news.title: Naukri, 99acres, few apps back on Google Play Store
news.para: ​IT and Telecom Minister Ashwini Vaishnaw, in an interview with PTI, said removal of apps cannot be permitted and that "startups will get the protection they need".
